FGCluster updates¶

2020/03/05 Giuseppe, Josquin, Davide

  1. Uncertainties on spectral parameters from realistic simulations with Multigrid approach, 1000 simulations from Josquin (2 weeks presentation ), obtained as the std dev estimated on each pixel across the 1000 maps.
  2. Derive new clusters with these uncertainties
  3. Minimize a new partition
    • for K in range(Kmin, Kmax)
    • estimate K clusters given the map of uncertaintes
    • get stat. and sys power spectra residuals given K patches
    • estimate variance as $$ \sigma _X =\sum_{\ell} (2\ell +1)C_{\ell, X}^{BB}\quad with \quad X=sys, stat $$ The more the clusters, the higher Stat. residuals ( increases with K, overpartition ). the more the clusters, the lower Sys. residuals (decreases with K underpartition)
  4. Optimal K : where $\sigma_{tot} = \sqrt{\sigma_{stat} ^2+ \sigma_{sys} ^2 }$ is minimum
  5. Josquin implemented a new component separation routine which essentially can get as input patches estimated singularly for each spectral parameter, (no need anymore of pairing clusters etc... ), under testing phase.

Therefore so far, I modified the sky configuration parameters so that we have just Bd varying and kept both Td and Bs constant .
